<p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">Published June 15, 2026 · 5 min read</p>

<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">The -URE suffix is a compact, efficient word-ending that creates nouns from verbs (mix→mixture, expose→exposure) using just 3 letters. While the suffix itself carries only 3 base points, its brevity means more letters go toward high-value roots. With over 200 valid -URE words in SOWPODS, this suffix punches above its weight in competitive play.</p>

<p>The real strength of -URE is efficiency — at only 3 tiles, it leaves 4 tiles for the root in a 7-letter bingo, allowing power consonants like X, Z, and J to dominate the scoring.</p>

<p>Knowing -URE words also helps defensively — you can spot when opponents are fishing for FIXTURE or SEIZURE and block the premium squares they need.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Why -URE Matters in Scrabble</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
